it is more about cost and risk.

263
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:47,220
A single training run might need thousands

264
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:49,110
upon thousands of GPU's and take months—

265
00:08:49,110 --> 00:08:50,300
and if it crashes midway,

266
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:52,190
that’s pretty much money down the drain.

267
00:08:52,310 --> 00:08:55,240
Plus, in this fiercely competitive large language model scene,

268
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:58,030
falling behind even for a moment—well, that’s a huge risk.

269
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,910
Of course, we should be wary

270
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:02,100
of over hyping our models’ abilities,

271
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:04,890
while also showing more patience and openness.

272
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,140
Understand that this process of training

273
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:10,130
a large language model —much like alchemy—involves many costs,

274
00:09:10,130 --> 00:09:12,180
risks, and non technical factors to weigh.

275
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:14,270
Uh, here is hoping China’s large language model

276
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:15,710
can go even further down this path!

277
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:16,270
Go!
